    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-09-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 587.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Valera</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-09-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 28,
                                    1885</date>. (Received October 2.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of his
                            Majesty the King of Spain, has the honor to inform the Hon. Thomas F.
                            Bayard, Secretary of State of the United States, that, as he is informed
                            by the consul-general of his nation at New York, the Cuban
                            revolutionists are preparing to celebrate in that city the anniversary
                            of the outbreak of the insurrection of 1868, for which purpose they have
                            already appointed a committee of arrangements.</p>
                <p>The undersigned minister, in bringing this matter to the knowledge of the
                            honorable Secretary of State, does so solely in order that the
                            administration may be prepared to repress any expedition against the
                            peace and tranquillity of the island of Cuba that the insurrectionists
                            may, perchance, desire to set on foot as a concomitant to their
                            aforesaid celebration.</p>
                <p>The undersigned, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JUAN VALERA.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
